      <title>FedEx robots could soon be delivering packages</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANFedEx could soon be carrying packages to your home via a delivery robot.FedEx plans to use robots to automate its delivery system, the Washington Post reports.The company is teaming up with DEKA Development & Research Corp to create the delivery robot, which is to be tested this summer. The robot, called FedEx SameDay Bot, is powered by batteries that are attached to its wheels. Cameras and software to avoid obstacles will be incorporated into the robot. The self-driving vehicle will be able to travel up to speeds of 10 miles per hour as it drives on sidewalks and roadways.According to Reuters, the robots will be used to handle home deliveries for companies such as Walmart and Pizza Hut.The robot will complement the company's SameDay City service, according to a FedEx press release.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. FedEx's delivery robot2. Features of the self-driving vehicle3. The delivery robot on the road4. The delivery robot delivering a packageVOICEOVER (in English): "The Washington Post reports FedEx plans to use robots to automate its delivery system.""The robot, called FedEx SameDay Bot, is powered by batteries that are attached to its wheels. Cameras and software to avoid obstacles will also be incorporated into the robot.""The self-driving vehicle will be able to travel up to speeds of 10 miles per hour as it drives on sidewalks and roadways.""According to Reuters, the robots will be used to handle home deliveries for companies such as Walmart and Pizza Hut."SOURCES: The Washington Post, Reuters, FedEx press release, FedEx SameDay Bot, https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/02/27/your-next-fedex-delivery-could-be-pizza/?noredirect=on&utm_term=.7a5c31285daehttps