e Empire State Building and the Top of the Rock at the Rockefeller Center, which measure 1,050 feet or 320 meters above street level and 850 feet or 260 meters above street level respectively."SOURCES: CNN, NJ.comhttps://www.cnn.com/travel/article/new-york-edge-observation-deck/index.htmlhttps://www.nj.com/news/2019/03/the-tallest-observation-deck-in-the-western-hemisphere-is-coming-to-new-york-knee-buckling-views-of-nj-included.html***]]></description>
