      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA Turkish man has been arrested following a possible shooting on a tram in Utrecht.The BBC reports that the shooting took place around 10:45 a.m. on board a tram in Utrecht's 24 Oktoberplein junction.According to the New York Times, witness accounts indicate that someone had activated the emergency brakes, as passengers screamed and clamored to escape.Reuters reports that at least three people were killed and nine others injured. According to the New York Times, some were wounded by shattering glass.After the gunman stepped off the tram, the Telegraph reports that he escaped in a stolen red Renault Clio. Police conducted house-to-house raids and arrested the suspect after an eight-hour manhunt.Authorities initially said the shooting was a terrorist incident, but later said they were not ruling out a personal motive.According to Turkey's Anadolu news agency, relatives of 37-year-old suspect Gokmen Tanis said the shooting was due to a family dispute. They alleged that only one person  possibly his former wife  was the intended target.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Shooting inside Utrecht tram2. Emergency brake activated, passengers running from tram3. Three people killed, nine injured4. Suspect arrested after manhuntVOICEOVER (in English): "The BBC reports that the shooting took place at around 10:45 a.m. on board a tram in Utrecht's 24 Oktoberplein junction.""According to the New York Times, witness accounts indicate that someone had activated the emergency brakes, as passengers screamed and clamored to escape.""Reuters reports that at least three people were killed and nine others injured. According to the New York Times, some were wounded by shattering glass.""After the gunman stepped off the tram, the Telegraph reports that he escaped in a stolen red Renault Clio.""Police conducted house-to-house raids and arrested the suspect after an eight-hour manhunt."SOURCES: BBC, New York Times, Telegraph, Reutershttps://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-47615231https://www.nytimes.com/2019/03/18/world/europe/utrecht-shooting.htmlhttps://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/03/18/utrecht-shooting-several-injured-shooting-utrecht-tram/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-netherlands-shooting-casualties/three-dead-nine-injured-in-utrecht-shooting-mayor-idUSKCN1QZ1NI***]]></description>
